Sentencas: La2CuO4 nanotubes are successfully synthesized by electro-spinning technology.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of La2CuO4 Nanotube Materials Prepared via Electrospinning Method

Sentencas: The structure and morphology of the materials are characterized by XRD, TG-DTA and SEM, respectively.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of La2CuO4 Nanotube Materials Prepared via Electrospinning Method

Sentencas: The results show that La2CuO4 nanotubes with an average diameter of 150 nm are obtained after sintering at 700 degrees C for 2 h. The La2CuO4 nanotube forms sufficient connection with each other, and good contact with the electrolyte after sintering at 900 degrees C for 0.5 h. Comparing the results obtained by Electrochemical Impedance Spectroscopy (EIS), it is clearly observed that the nanotube cathode exhibits superior performance than the powder cathode.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of La2CuO4 Nanotube Materials Prepared via Electrospinning Method

Sentencas: The area specific resistance (ASR) of the nanotube cathode is 1.03 Omega.cm(2) at 700 degrees C in air, whereas for the powder one with the same composition, the ASR is 1.61 Omega.cm(2).
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of La2CuO4 Nanotube Materials Prepared via Electrospinning Method

Sentencas: The oxygen partial pressure measurement indicates that the charge transfer process is the rate-limiting step of the nanotube electrode reactions.
Titulo: Electrochemical Performance of La2CuO4 Nanotube Materials Prepared via Electrospinning Method
